The paper proposes a new method for rank aggregation that rectifies the underlying data distribution directly and aligns it to the homogeneous data assumption without involving any noise model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it deals with developing a new method for data analysis. Additionally, the paper involves Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
